Great SmokeShack (the cherry peppers and bacon match wonderfully) and the Black & White Shake was delicious. Crinkle cut fries seem generic in the time of fresh hand cut fries, but they aren't meant to be the star of the show anyway.

When you go to Shake Shack, get a shake! I originally ordered a chocolate spice holiday shake, but come to find out, it has cookies in it and therefore wasn't gluten-free. Thankfully, I marked my order as avoiding wheat and gluten, so the person at the counter informed me that the one I picked wasn't gluten-free and let me change my order. What I left with was a black and white (fudge and vanilla) shake with cinnamon added and whipped cream on top- it was delicious! Can't say I was surprised I enjoyed it so much because it featured two of my favorite things: rich, dark chocolate and cinnamon. Think I'm going to order that again if I find myself at Shake Shack in the future.  They have a gluten-free bun option.  All the employees I saw were wearing their masks properly and people seemed to be well social distanced.
